    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Drug Bust or Trap?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr Arthur G Krohn letter comments on August 19 article on tactics of undercover narcotics teams in setting up drug busts</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Lawyers Say Drug War's Tactics Draw Addicts Into Serious Crime'' (news article, Aug. 19): Undercover police teams that try to get recovering heroin users to sell their weekend supplies of methadone as they leave their clinics are nothing short of inhumane. Calling that a drug bust is bizarre and sharply underscores the futility of the war on drugs.</p>
        <p>ARTHUR G. KROHN, M.D.  Scarsdale, N.Y., Aug. 20, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
